insert into public.noticia_ml (id, titulo, descripcion, idioma)
values(1,'Happy Halloween to you from the anime industry!',
'Halloween, a holiday originating in the West, has found a special place in the heart of Japan, and to commemorate it, various Japanese artists have created an astonishing variety of anime illustrations. Despite its origins in the West, the celebration has gained popularity in Japan in a unique and significant way. Halloween, celebrated on October 31, is characterized by costumes and fun, but it also has deep roots in Celtic tradition like Samhain, marking the end of summer and the beginning of winter. Despite its pagan background, Halloween has become a global holiday with a distinctive twist in each country. In Japan, Halloween has become increasingly popular in recent decades, and this is partly due to the influence of popular culture, including anime and manga. Young Japanese have embraced the opportunity to dress up in extravagant costumes, inspired by their favorite anime and video game characters, and participate in parades and events themed around this celebration. The anime illustrations that have been created in commemoration of Halloween reflect the creativity and passion of Japanese artists. From iconic anime characters dressed in spooky costumes to animated landscapes filled with pumpkins and ghosts, these illustrations capture the festive spirit of Halloween with a Japanese twist.',
'en_US');

