'We have previously talked about GEM Partners, a Japanese company that conducts weekly surveys to find out what the most viewed content is on television and streaming services in Japan. Although these surveys began with a participation small enough to be considered relevant, the most recent reports indicate the participation of more than 24,500 people through the companys media, mostly electronic. However, the companys methods are still questionable, since they generally ask what respondents have recently watched on streaming services. This means that they are not popularity polls for the season currently broadcast, since someone could say that they “watched Dragon Ball recently” and this would count as a point towards this franchise within this list. Even so, it seems that the results are attracting attention among opinion forums in Japan, since the ranking for the third week of October-2023 (10/17/2023~10/23/2023) positioned Jujutsu Kaisen in the first position, followed by SPY x FAMILY and Sousou no Frieren (Frieren: Beyond Journeys End). Popularity Ranking in Streaming Services (Week 3 of October-2023) 1. Jujutsu Kaisen 2nd Season. 2. SPY x FAMILY 2nd Season. 3. Sousou no Frieren. 4. Detective Conan. 5.One Piece. 6. Last One Standing (live-action program). 7. Silent Parade (live-action movie). 8. Oshi no Ko. 9. Kimetsu no Yaiba. 10. Rurouni Kenshin. 11. The Eminence in Shadow. 12. Professional Baseball (live-action program). 13. Jigen Daisuke (live-action program). 14. Kingdom. 15. Dragon Ball. And of course, the results immediately caught the attention of Japanese Internet users: «What is this ranking about? I dont understand what Dragon Ball is doing on the list. It seems that they have changed the survey method to cover more people, but even so I dont think the results are reliable. Detective Conan and One Piece are still strong despite the years. Im getting the feeling that Kusuriya no Hitorigoto will hit the ground running this season, which is why it just premiered. «Blue Lock was a failure in terms of streaming and Blu-ray / DVD sales, but the original work and all the merchandise are selling like hot cakes. Whats the point of all this?. This whole season has been rubbish, I havent seen any premiere that caught my attention. Be that as it may, this ranking shows that the only interesting content in this country is anime. «There is a tendency for the second and third seasons to fall in momentum. But it seems that both Jujutsu Kaisen and SPY x FAMILY are being the exception to the rule. I think this second season of SPY x FAMILY is being too underrated. It also turns out that, having passed a month since the start of the Fall-2023 season (October-December), the popular Japanese media Anime!Anime! conducted its usual popularity survey where it asked its readers for their favorite series so far, and the results were the following: 1. Sousou no Frieren. 2. SPY x FAMILY 2nd Season. 3. Kusuriya no Hitorigoto. 4. Dr. STONE NEW WORLD Part 2. 5. Tokyo Revengers: Tenjiku-hen. 6. The Idolmaster Million Live!. 7. HYPNOSIS MIC -Division Rap Battle- Rhyme Anima 2nd Season. 8. HYPNOSIS MIC -Division Rap Battle- Rhyme Anima. 9. After School Hanako-kun. 10. Undead Unluck.',
